				\begin{document}$${{\rm{SMDW}}}_{{\rm{subnational}}}=\frac{{{\rm{SMDW}}}_{{\rm{national}}}}{{{\rm{ALB}}}_{{\rm{national}}}}{\times {\rm{ALB}}}_{{\rm{subnational}}},$$\end{document}where ALBnational, ALBsubnational and SMDWnational are known values.

Climate variables GHI and T were matched to ERA5-Land parameters ‘Surface solar radiation downwards’ (converted from cumulative to mean hourly) and ‘2 metre temperature’ (converted from K to °C), respectively. RH was calculated from the ambient and dew point temperature parameters in a relationship derived from the August–Roche–Magnus approximation61 rearranged as:RH=100%×eaTdb+TdeaTb+T\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
